description: 1967 Ford Thunderbird Landau 2D Hardtop
The Ford Thunderbird was redesigned in 1967. The very stylish front grill was based on the air intake of jet fighters from that era.
The retractable headlights are hidden in the grill, which gives the car an even stronger appearance.
A real sight for sore eyes!
The Thunderbird has many options:
- Power Windows
- Air Conditioning
-Disc Brakes
- Power Steering
- Power Brakes
The paint is very nice and matches perfectly with the look of the car. The chrome has some signs of use, but is in good condition.
The beautiful black vinyl top is amazing.
The interior is finished with beautiful stainless steel details.
Both the front and rear seats are very well maintained. The headliner and the carpet are in a very good condition.
The dashboard is very stylish decorated.
The Thunderbird has a beautiful White Wall tires with sporty rims.

Gateway Classic Cars welcomes this iconic luxury car a 1963 Ford Thunderbird to its Philadelphia showroom located in West Deptford NJ! Ford had introduced the T-Bird in 1955 to counter Chevy"??s Corvette and something clicked with buyers as the T-bird line continued to impress throughout the years.  Interestingly the Thunderbird departed from the performance market starting in the late 50s and was transformed into a signature luxury vehicle. The 1963 Thunderbird represented the last year of the third generation of the car and features some changes including AM/FM Radio and vacuum assisted door locks.  This car boasts the sleek styling of the third generation Thunderbirds and conveys the quintessential space age designs as seen on both the exterior and interior.  Wearing beautiful black paint done in 2014 this car conveys some serious class with T-bird emblems rocket taillights and streamlined front and rear.  Open the door and move over the steering wheel with ease. Take note of the classy beige interior redone in early 2017 featuring front power bucket seats large center console. New dashboard/padding and attractive an instrument panel.  Powering this vehicle is the original 390CID V8 linked to a three-speed cruise-o-matic transmission that gets you down the road with ease!  Don"??t let this black beauty get away!  Give our friendly sales staff a call and take this gorgeous car home today! Stk. 2233  1963 Ford Thunderbird

The third-generation Thunderbird was manufactured between 1961 and 1963. The ''Bullet Bird'' was a timeless design, featuring Ford's trademark ''rocket engine'' taillights, sharp rear tailfins and 'somewhat' restrained chrome ornamentation. This partially restored 1963 Thunderbird is a piece of Blue Oval lore, virtually as beautiful today as it was on the showroom floor. The classic lines are complimented by a Champaign exterior and matching original vinyl interior. The luxury T'bird was fully equipped for the era including: air conditioning, AM radio, power windows, and power driver seat. For ease of entry and exit, the steering wheel assembly slides 10'' to the right. Horsepower is furnished by a 300bhp 390ci-4V engine with factory chrome accents. The owner believes it to be the original FE motor - running superbly and never rebuilt. It is backed by Ford's classic 3-speed Cruise-O-Matic transmission. Power steering and power drum brakes were included as standard equipment and radial tires are mounted on factory wheels with original spinner hubcaps. There are very few of these classic Thunderbirds around for the serious Ford hobbyist, far fewer in this condition. This one belongs in your collection.
